OL,5, In our series of letters from African  
OL,6, writers, Nigerian novelist Adaobi      
OL,7, Tricia Nwaubani looks at the growing   
OL,8, frustration among the middle-class that
OL,9, is pushing people to leave her country.
OL,11,FA few years ago, my childhood friend   
OL,12,Fmoved back to Nigeria after being in   
OL,13,Fthe US for more than 20 years studying 
OL,14,Fand working.                           
OL,16,FBut, despite joining a successful      
OL,17,Fcorporation in Lagos, earning a decent 
OL,18,Fsalary, and living in the upmarket     
OL,19,FLekki district, she was soon ready to  
OL,20,Fpack up and return to America.         
